  "text": "If you're into #scraping and #Python, you should probably know that there's a new cool kid in town.\n\nJust a few days ago Apify has released #Crawlee, a new open source scraping framework in Python.\n\nIt's in asyncio and has type hints. It can seamlessly switch between basic and full-browser (Playwright) requests. Automatic retries, proxy rotation, etc.\n\nI'm very much #Scrapy person, but these promises get me really intrigued. Also I like the fact that for a large part the framework is made in Brno, a city I have close to my heart ❤️ Shout out to Vláďa Dušek!\n\nCheck it out! And if you're at #EuroPython, visit their booth with Saurav Jain. Tell them what you think! At the booth or in GitHub issues 😀",
